title: For Sale:  Military History Library @300 books
postcontent:
These books include many written by those who were there. They include the Civil War, WWI, WWII, Korea, Vietnam, Iraq. Several are written and self published by WWII veterans and are very hard to find. Includes the book written by the last Japanese soldier to surrender in the Philippines in the 70's. Many about survival and escape and histories and biographies of famous Generals, Patton, Wainwright, Chesty Puller, etc. Though most concern WWII, there are 15 or so about the Civil war. Among these are two volumes written by Jefferson Davis. There is also a volume written by Sam Houston and published in the mid 1800's. 5 volumes published by the US Army on Pacific campaigns.

There are too many to list or describe here, but If you are interested, I have them all cataloged in an excell spreadsheet which I can send. All of the books have been read, some many times, by me. Some are like new, while others are old and worn, but they contain knowledge which is being lost these days. The things contained in these books will never be taught in schools. I've been collecting these books and reading them for more than 20 years now. I'm getting older and I don't want them to wind up in some garage sale or donated to a library who'd throw most of them away.

If you're interested, I can send more pictures, but it may take a few days. Some are valuable, $20-$30 or more and I've never seen A copy of the Sam Houston book. Most would be in the $5 - $10 dollar range at half-priced books, and if a person wanted to, he could double or tripple his money selling them online. The titles in the photos are a cross section of the group. There is a heavy emphisis on the Marine Corps and some on the SeaBees too. If you tried to accumulate this collection, first of all it would take years, and counting shipping and gas to go to bookstores, it could easily cost $3000 - $5000, if you could find them.

I can't tell who may want them, but I'd like to see them go to someone who would read and appreciate them. I won't sell them separately. If I can't sell them all in one bunch, I'll donate them to the VA library. I've got a feeling they'll weigh 250-300# so crating and shipping might be an issue.

Hope someone wants them.

Its proprietary magazines are also polymer.[2] The handguards are also polymer, and feature quadruple Picatinny rails.[1] The M&P15-22 can be used as a cheaper alternative for training with an AR-15 style rifle, since the rifle itself is much less expensive than most AR-15s, and the ammunition may often be one tenth the price of normal .223 Remington/5.56x45mm NATO, allowing the owner to enjoy far more range time for the same cost in ammunition. While shooting .22 LR is not a perfect substitute for training with the rifle's "true" cartridge, it can be a good way to focus on basic marksmanship and handling skills without the cost or recoil associated with shooting larger cartridges. The rifle features a safety and bolt lock that operate just like an AR-15. The M&P15-22 can also be an alternative in jurisdictions that restrict magazine capacity for centerfire cartridges. This is available in Magpul FDE (Field Dark Earth), and standard black. Because the M&P15-22 fires a rimfire cartridge, it can be used as a legal way to shoot large numbers of cartridges without reloading. The M&P15-22's lower recoil may also be used as a way to ease new shooters into the sport, allowing them to familiarize themselves with AR-15 controls without the fear of excessive recoil or noise.
